A 16-year-old boy drowned at Durban’s North Beach on Saturday, 22 February. KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said: ” Police divers from Durban SAPS Search and Rescue and Metro Police Search and Rescue were called out to recover the body of a 16-year-old victim from the shoreline near North Beach.” Mbele said that the body was later found at Durban’s Wedge Beach. Police have opened an inquest docket at Durban Central police station for investigation. Meanwhile in another incident, police officers from Metro Police Search and Rescue and Durban SAPS Search and Rescue and other role players responded to a drowning incident, between eThekwini and Jet Si Beach on Sunday, 23 February. Mbele said that two swimmers got into difficulty leading to a 25-year-old drowning. ” A search was conducted but the victim was not found. The search continues,” said Mbele. This is a developing story and updates will follow as events unfold.